        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Typically displayed at the bottom of a window, status bars have "panes," which include "indicators" and a "message line."</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The indicators give the status of such things as SCROLL LOCK, whether macro recording is turned on, and so on.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The message line on the status bar can display information about program status or about a toolbar button or menu item that the user is pointing to with the mouse.</source>
